    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-05-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/346</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kornfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received June 25.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 510</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise the Department that
                    Mr. James Grant Forbes of Blair &amp; Company, New York, left Teheran on May 19
                    for America to confer with his company regarding the loan which the Persian
                    Government seeks to obtain in America. Before his departure, Mr. Forbes had a
                    conference with the Prime Minister, Dr. A. C. Millspaugh, Administrator General
                    of Finances, and the Minister of Finance at which it was decided to pledge all
                    of Persia’s revenues as security for this loan.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph S. Kornfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
